 ## Purpose
-This procedure outlines the steps to be taken when handling Data Subject Access Requests (DSARs) in accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
+This procedure outlines the steps to be taken when handling Data Subject Access Requests (DSARs) in accordance with applicable data protection laws.
 
 ## Intake & Verification
-1. Identify and verify the requestor's identity.
-2. Confirm that the request is a DSAR under GDPR.
-3. Check if the request is time-barred or incomplete.
-
-### Safeguards
-* Lawful bases: Consent, Contract, Legal Obligation (declared in ctx.lawful_bases.declared)
-* Processors: Controller, Joint Controller, Processor (listed in ctx.processors)
+1. Identify and acknowledge receipt of a DSAR from an individual.
+2. Verify the identity of the requester using the information provided.
+3. Check if the request is complete and includes all necessary details.
 
 ## Assessment & Coordination
-1. Determine the scope of the request.
-2. Identify relevant data and systems involved.
-3. Assess the feasibility of providing the requested information.
-
-### Safeguards
-* Transfers: Adequacy, SCC, BCR (mechanisms listed in ctx.transfers[0].mechanisms)
-* Retention: 1 month retention period (defined in ctx.retention.months)
+1. Determine the lawful basis for processing the personal data requested, referencing [lawful bases](#lawful_bases) in ctx.
+2. Identify any processors involved in the processing of the data, as listed in [processors](#processors) in ctx.
+3. Assess if any transfers of personal data have occurred, referencing [transfers](#transfers) in ctx.
+4. Determine the retention period for the requested data, referencing [retention](#retention) in ctx.
 
 ## Response Content
-1. Provide a response within the specified timeframe.
-2. Include all requested information, excluding sensitive data.
-3. Offer an explanation for any withheld or redacted information.
-
-### Safeguards
-* Rights: Data subject's rights under GDPR (referenced in ctx.sections.E.Rights)
-* Security controls: Implemented security measures to protect personal data (listed in ctx.security_measures)
+1. Provide a clear and concise response to the requester, including:
+	* A description of the personal data processed.
+	* The purposes for which the data was collected and processed.
+	* Any third parties with whom the data has been shared.
+	* Details on how the individual's rights have been exercised.
+2. Include information on applicable security controls, such as encryption and access controls.
 
 ## Timelines & Escalations
-1. Respond to DSARs within 30 days.
-2. Escalate complex or high-priority requests to the Data Protection Officer (DPO).
-
-### Safeguards
-* Risk rating: Strong risk rating (defined in ctx.risk.rating)
-* Earned scores: A.Context, B.Stakeholders, B.Transfers, C.Risk, D.Security, E.Rights, F.Residual (listed in ctx.sections)
+1. Respond to DSARs within [30 calendar days](https://ico.org.uk/for-organisations/guide-to-data-protection/guide-to-the-general-data-protection-regulation-gdpr/data-subject-requests/) of receipt.
+2. Escalate complex or high-priority requests to the Data Protection Officer (DPO) or designated team.
 
 ## Recordkeeping
-1. Maintain a record of all DSARs received.
-2. Document the response and any actions taken.
-
-### Safeguards
-* Processor details: Controller, Joint Controller, Processor (listed in ctx.processors)
-* Transfer mechanisms: Adequacy, SCC, BCR (mechanisms listed in ctx.transfers[0].mechanisms)
+1. Maintain a record of all DSARs received, including:
+	* Requester's details and contact information.
+	* Date and time of receipt.
+	* Response provided.
+2. Store records securely in accordance with [retention](#retention) policies.
 
